    {
      "instruction": "<p>Rinse the<strong> red lentils </strong>in a sieve under <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> red lentils</strong> and <strong>green</strong> <strong>lentils </strong>(no need to drain) to the softened onion</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> to the lentils and cook for 15-20 min, stirring occasionally, until all the water is absorbed and the lentils are tender and porridge-like in consistency</p>",
